<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-660-546  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 660 546.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 12 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI switches to new data center. (MCI Communications Corp)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     UpgradingTelecommunicationsSoftware ModificationInformation CentersNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MCI SWITCHES TO NEW DATA CENTER NORTH ROYALTON, OHIO, U.S.A., 1989 SEP 7 (NB)-- If your MCI Mail service has been out for a time recently, it's probably anormal glitch in the cut-over of MCI's new communications center in NorthRoyalton, Ohio.andP;  Once the cutover is complete, MCI officials assert, thenetwork will &quot;literally think for itself.&quot; Total MCI offices at NorthRoyalton now come to 160,000 square feet.andP;  Besides network management, theMCI center will also handle billing.andP;  Software controls the whole building,which is based on IBM mainframes and 4 robotic tape silos.andP;  A vice presidentexplained what the software does at the center's dedication.andP;  &quot;It watchesitself.andP;  Does it smell smoke? Is a door ajar? Is it getting too warm inside?andO;It's aware of most everything that's happening in the building, and it takeswhatever action is needed immediately.andP;  It turns up the air conditioning;alerts somebody that the door is open; sends an alarm and turns on the firesuppression equipment if that's needed.&quot; Makes you wish MCI were designingteenagers.andP;  (Dana Blankenhorn/19890908/Press Contact: Douglas Dome of MCIMidwest, 312-938-4995)</TEXT></DOC>